irect\" and create a new `Term` for `Exclude URLs` **without checking** \"Regular Expression\".\r\n```\r\n/database/\r\n```\r\n- Go to frontend and enter again not existing URL \r\n`example.org/database/db.sql.gz` (replace example.org with your domain).\r\n\r\n- Check backend > Components > Redirects.\r\n\r\n### Expected result\r\n- Above URL is **NOT** collected by plugin.\r\n\r\n### Actual result\r\n- Above URL is collected by plugin.\r\n\r\n### Additional comments\r\n- One have to enter \r\n```\r\ndatabase/\r\n```\r\nin Term field instead of \r\n```\r\n/database/\r\n```\r\nBut that would also block mydatabase/ and similiar URLs.\r\n \r\nPlease don't comment that I should use a regular expression in this case ;-) I know that it's possible but from my point of view that's not obvious for users and not an expected behavior. ","score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/joomla/joomla-cms/issues/19955","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/joomla/joomla-cms","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/joomla/joomla-cms/issues/19955/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/joomla/joomla-cms/issues/19955/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/joomla/joomla-cms/issues/19955/events","html_url":"https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/issues/19955","id":307083189,"number":19955,"title":"Question: Why doesn't Joomla have a standard feature to make te admin url secret?","user":{"login":"JSWebdesign","id":8665392,"avatar_url":"https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/8665392?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/JSWebdesign","html_url":"https://github.com/JSWebdesign","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JSWebdesign/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JSWebdesign/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JSWebdesign/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/JSWebdesign/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users